column5: Fruits large, 14 inches by 15 inches, yellow.
A hardy squash with wonderful flavor; germinates well and needs little care besides appropriate watering.
Oblate shaped friut; 6 - 10 inches by 4 - 5.5 inches with grooves, flesh orange 1 to 1.5 inches thick.
Male sterile F.  Segregates (approximately) 1 normal to 1 male sterile. Vigorous, bush type. Fruits many, oblate 1 to 1.25 inches, light orange.
Selection made from PI 176536. Fruits oblate, 8 by 10 inches; ribs 1 inch wide; flesh light yellow.

Male sterile C.  Buttercup type. Segregates (approximately) 1 normal to 1 male sterile. Vigorous, medium maturing, medium-sized vines. Fruits many, oblate turbinate 4.25 by 6 to 9 inches, dark green; 4.5 pounds; flesh .75 to 1.25 inches, orange.
Donated by L.O. Melis.  Seeds small, white, almost marginless.  Local name Alayo.
Donated by L.O. Melis.  Bush type.  Seeds white, margins white.  Local name Tanca.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Seeds medium-sized, white, with slight sculpturing, margins light. Local name Sayanca.
Seeds white, medium-sized, margins present. Local name Zapallito del Tronco (Cochi magnif.).
Seeds white, medium-sized, margins present. Local name Campana-Labanda-70.
Donated by L.O. Melis.  Bush type.  Seeds small, white, margins light. Local name Maguilta.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Seeds large, white, margins light. Local name Carla.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Bush type. Seeds white, marginless. Local name Supupa.
Donated by L.O. Melis.  Seeds white, sculptured, marginless.  Local name Vistalba.
Probably a mixture of local types. Local name Zapallo.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Bush type. Seeds white, margins present. Local name Sipigua.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Seeds white, margins almost white. Local name Chinque.
Seeds Banana type, large, tan, margins broad, light. Local name Plomo ruso (Plaunorskja).
Donated by J. Camara-Hernandez. Seeds Banana type, large, golden brown, margins  lighter.
Donated by L.O. Melis.  Bush type.  Seeds white, margins light.  Local name Choay.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Bush type. Seeds medium-sized, roundish, white, margins light. Local name Vinaca.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Bush type. Seeds medium-sized, white, more or less marginless. Local name Taplop.
Bush type plant. Prolific in fruiting.
Donated by J. Camara-Hernandez.  Seeds medium-sized, pure white, margins same color.
Seeds white, small, margins broad. Local name Zipinki Campana.
Fruit surface rough. Probably from Misiones. Local name Zapallo.
Fruit surface rough. Flesh yellow, thick. Seeds large, yellow. Probably from Misiones. Local name Zapallo.
Donated by L.O. Melis.  Winter bush type.  Seeds large, white, margins white.  Local name Marino de Mendoza.
Donated by J. Camara-Hernandez. Seeds large, white, margins slightly darker.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Bush type. Fruit white. Local name Naclao.
Fruit medium-sized, Probably elongate, with a rough surface. Probably from Misiones. Local name Zapallo.
Seeds large, dirty white, margins present. Local name Capana-Ingles.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Bush type. Fruit solid white. Local name Tabalque.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Seeds large, white, margins white. Local name Anton.
Donated by J. Camara-Hernandez. Seeds medium-sized, white, margins white.
Donated by J. Camara-Hernandez. Seeds medium to large, white, margins darker.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Bush type. Seeds medium-sized, white, more or less marginless. Local name Chacoriano.
Donated by J. Camara-Hernandez.  Seeds medium-sized, creamy white, margins darker.
Probably a mixture of local types. Local name Zapallo.
Fruit medium-sized with deep vein tracts, rough surface. Probably from Misiones. Local name Zapallo.
Probably imported from Misiones.  Fruit flattish, smooth surface, orange, medium vein tracts, light color, producing stripes.  Flesh lemon, thin.  Seed cavity large. Local name Zapallo.
Donated by L.O. Melis. Seeds small, white, margins light. Local name Pallamay.
Probably imported from Misiones. Fruit yellow, rough surface, deep vein tracts,  skin orange. Flesh yellow. Local name Zapallo.
Sown May, harvested October.  Used as adornment

Fruit oblong elipsoid. Fruit lenght 39cm, width 57.5cm. diameter 19.5cm, weight 5.16kg. Average seed yeild 263, seed weight 20gm.  present. Leaves pinnately and deeply lobed, small size with smooth margins. Days to germination in field 7.3. Days to 50% flowering 72.3. Average stem length 161.3, rounded with tendrils present. Leaves cordate, large, dented with shallow lobes.
Fruit flat, ribbed, about 14 inches in diameter; color brownish-gray; flesh deep orange, about 2 inches thick; late maturing.
Fruit subvoid, 15 inches in diameter, ashy, unribbed.
Fruit elongate, 25 by 10 inches, ashy, unribbed; not sweet but tasty; flesh 2 1/2 inches thick and orange-colored.
Fruit subglobose, 15 by 12 inches, heavily ribbed, grey, squash-type. Not sweet but tasty.
Fruit subglobose, 15 inches long, faintly ribbed, creamy white; flest pale orange, 1.5 to 2.5 inches thick, and incipid.
Fruit subglobose, 17 inches long, rind salmon, with deeply indented ribs; flesh salmon, 2.75 inches thick, and incipid.
Fruit 15 by 8 inches; rind orange red to paler, splotched with green, pinkish-white incomplete rib lines and heavily indented ribs; flesh orange, 2 inches thick, tender and insipid.
Said to be globose. Gorwn where summers are hot.
Fruit elongate, 9 by 15 inches, rind gray green and unribbed; flesh yellow, 2 inches thich, and insipid.
Fruit flattened, 11 inches long and 7 inches in diameter, deeply ribbed, orange red; flesh 5 inches thick, greenish yellow, firm, low in sugar.
Fruit reddish-orange, up to 2 feet in diameter.
Fruit pear-shaped, reddish, to 6 inches in diameter and 1 foot long.
PI book claims this acc. is C.Pepo.
Fruit globose, 12 inches long, pale salmon; flesh orange, 1.5 to 2.5 inches thick, insipid.
Fruit 18 inches long and 9 inches in diameter, orange red, with faint irregular ridb; flesh 1.25 inches thick, deep yellow, good quality.
Fruit globose, 14 inches long, with deep irregular ribs, salmon, mottled paler; flesh 2 to 4 inches thick, pale orange, insipid.
Fruit not seen; seeds medium sized, dark brown, margin same as seeds.

Reported to have come from local market. Vine typical maxima, poor vigor; fruit flattened 15 by 25 cm.; grayish mottled skin, smooth; very hard; flesh well colored, thick. Seeds yellowish brown, margin light brown. Fruit 'Hubbard' type.
Fruit about 15 cm. diameter, 30 cm. long, skin light grayish green, warted overall; very hard skin; thin flesh, light salmon. Seeds light brown with margin lighter than body.
A very large squash obtained through Dr. Hugh W. Hubbard, of Paotingfu, China.
Plants grown by Manjuy Indians for centuries, endemic. Seeds small, white. Local name Zapallo.
Seeds small, white. From Manjuy Indians. Local name Zapallo.
Originally from Thimphu. Sown April, harvested August-September. Fruits very large (20kg or more), less favorable than PI 481622, used for animal feed.
Local original source. Sown April, harvested September. Fruits large. Local name Brumsa Kathang.
Seeds white. Local name Nyamutumha and Nzururu.
Fruits white. Associated with pumpkins and other weedy, bitter watermelons.
Fruit shape elongated. Received as Cucurbita moschata.
Fruit oblong. Seeds white. Local name Mupusi.
Fruit 24 by 10 inches; rind battleship gray, shiny, faintly ribbed; flesh bright orange, of good quality, but not very sweet.
Fruit 14 by 9 inches; rind black green with blotches of Chinese red; flesh orange yellow, 2 to 2.25 inches thick, fair quality.
Fruit somewhat flattened, 10 by 9 inches; rind pea green, heavily indented ribs; flesh orange, 2 to 3 inches thick, falirly good.
Fruit subglobose, slightly flattened, 18 inches in length; weight about 50 pounds; rind grayish green; flesh yellow, 3 inches thick, not very sweet.
Fruits slightly flattened, 14 inches in length; rind salmon pink; flesh yellow, 2 inches thick, fair quality.
Fruits slightly flattened, 15 inches in length; rind obscurely ribbed, gray green; flesh yellow, 2.5 inches thick, fair quality.
Fruit somewhat flattened, 8 inches in length; rind black green; flesh orange, 1.5 inches thick, rather insipid.
Fruit somewhat flattened, 8 inches in length; rind orange red; flesh bright orange, 1.5 inches thick, of fair quality.
Fruit globose, 10 inches in diameter; rind white, faintly ribbed; flesh pale orange, 2 inches thick, incipid.
Fruit flattened, 16 by14 inches; rind orange pink, with broken blotches of green and white; flesh yellow, 2.5 inches thick, insipid.
Fruit 24 by 10 inches; rind smooth; unribbed, handsome salmon pink with green belly; flesh 2.5 inches thick, of good texture, and sweet.
Fruit globose, 8 inches in diameter; rind orange red, with rib stripes of salmon; ribs faintly indented; flesh 1 1/4 inches thick, greenish yellow and insipid. PI book claims this acc. is C.Pepo
Inbred selection. Vigorous, medium maturing, bush. Fruits oblate 4 by 7 to 9 inches, dark green with light stripes; 3.20 pounds; flesh .5 to 1.25  inches, orange.

Large, white to light green fruit. Round to elongated shape and blush pink when fully ripe. Apricot flesh is sweet. Good keeper.

Bush with short internodes. Fruits round oblate, 590 grams; shell hard, red orange; flesh dark gold orange, fine texture, no fiber, dense, 3 cm. thick; early; 8 per plant.
Inbred selection. Vigorous, medium maturing, bush. Fruits many, oblate 4.5 to 6.5 to 8 inches, dark green; 3.56 pounds; flesh 1 inch, bright orange.

Male sterile B. Segregates (approximately) 1 normal to 1 male sterile. Vigorous, medium maturing, semibush. Fruits oblate 7 to 9 by 8 to 12 inches, orange-red; 10 pounds; flesh 1.25 to 2.25 inches, orange.
Selected from an unknown PI number in 1938.

Note from Jesse Reil (donor):  Seed was harvested from Mammoth King seed acquired from the late Tom Knocke's collection that originally came from Gurney's Seeds back in the late 1970's - early 1980's.  The plants produced about 2 large pumpkins per vine.  The fruit is show-type; large and standardized with an almost florescent beige color.
